text: Saadia Sohail Rana () is a Pakistani politician who has been a Member of the Provincial Assembly of the Punjab, since May 2013. == Early life and education == She was born on 23 April 1968 in Lahore. She has the degree of Bachelor of Arts. == Political career == She was elected to the Provincial Assembly of the Punjab as a candidate of Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf on a reserved seat for women in Pakistani general election, 2013. == References == Category:1968 births Category:Living people
title: Saadia Sohail Rana
